what that means.

512
00:24:48.779 --> 00:24:49.939
- Okay. well...
- Do you mind?

513
00:24:49.989 --> 00:24:51.824
Let's just see what we got here.

514
00:24:51.908 --> 00:24:54.118
Hmm. the mezzanine.
that's where you are. but...

515
00:24:54.202 --> 00:24:56.054
- Okay.
- that just simply won't cut it.

516
00:24:56.078 --> 00:24:57.622
You see. you want
to be down here.

517
00:24:57.705 --> 00:24:59.373
The sound.
it just wraps around you

518
00:24:59.457 --> 00:25:01.626
like a fleece.

519
00:25:01.709 --> 00:25:03.520
How about I swap your ticket
with my aide when he arrives?

520
00:25:03.544 --> 00:25:05.671
Wouldn't he mind?

521
00:25:05.755 --> 00:25:07.590
Well. not if he wants
to keep his job.

522
00:25:07.673 --> 00:25:09.800
Please. take a seat.

523
00:25:09.884 --> 00:25:11.719
Thank you.

524
00:25:15.389 --> 00:25:17.808
In the bag.

525
00:25:17.892 --> 00:25:20.353
We go 13/14s.

526
00:25:20.436 --> 00:25:22.104
8/13s.

527
00:25:22.188 --> 00:25:24.190
Over seven months.
six-day working weeks.

528
00:25:24.273 --> 00:25:25.334
Maybe a time sheet
clocking hours?

529
00:25:25.358 --> 00:25:27.276
Maybe a ratings scale?

530
00:25:27.360 --> 00:25:28.444
I don't know.

531
00:25:28.527 --> 00:25:30.154
- Top you off?
- Yeah.

532
00:25:30.238 --> 00:25:31.447
Yes. ma'am.

533
00:25:32.448 --> 00:25:35.117
And when you get the chance.
could you bring me the bill?

534
00:25:35.201 --> 00:25:36.744
This guy doesn't have any money.

535
00:25:36.827 --> 00:25:39.121
Sure.
Let me tally it up for you.

536
00:25:39.205 --> 00:25:41.624
Great.

537
00:25:41.707 --> 00:25:43.709
- It's a tally.
- What?

538
00:25:43.793 --> 00:25:46.170
Here. 13/14ths.

539
00:25:46.254 --> 00:25:47.463
Something happened 13 times

540
00:25:47.546 --> 00:25:49.382
when it was supposed
to happen 14 times.

541
00:25:49.465 --> 00:25:51.801
Uh. here. 11 out of 13.
Eight out of 11.

542
00:25:54.220 --> 00:25:56.430
Hey. bud. I just...

543
00:25:56.514 --> 00:25:57.807
Okay. what did I tell you?

544
00:25:57.890 --> 00:26:00.810
Hands are for helping.
not hitting.

545
00:26:00.893 --> 00:26:02.728
Apologize to your brother.

546
00:26:02.812 --> 00:26:04.522
Share your Legos. okay?

547
00:26:04.605 --> 00:26:07.650
I love you.
To the moon and back.

548
00:26:07.733 --> 00:26:09.944
Okay. bye for now.

549
00:26:10.027 --> 00:26:12.530
Sorry.
I don't know why I gave them

550
00:26:12.613 --> 00:26:14.573
my burner number. uh...

551
00:26:16.284 --> 00:26:17.576
Well. you look happy.

552
00:26:17.660 --> 00:26:19.078
I did the math.

553
00:26:19.161 --> 00:26:22.999
There were 2.197 total events.
whatever they were.

554
00:26:23.082 --> 00:26:25.960
But they only succeeded
1.547 times.

555
00:26:26.043 --> 00:26:27.271
But that's not
the interesting number.

556
00:26:27.295 --> 00:26:28.397
Look how many times
they didn't get

557
00:26:28.421 --> 00:26:29.755
the outcome they wanted.

558
00:26:29.839 --> 00:26:33.592
2.197 minus 1.547.

559
00:26:35.261 --> 00:26:36.971
Six hundred and fifty.
Holy shit.

560
00:26:37.054 --> 00:26:39.724
Six fifty at 100K each.

561
00:26:39.807 --> 00:26:41.559
It's all connected somehow.

562
00:26:41.642 --> 00:26:43.269
So...

563
00:26:44.270 --> 00:26:47.440
So... hands are for helping?

564
00:26:49.066 --> 00:26:50.860
You have brass knuckles
in your pocket.

565
00:26:50.943 --> 00:26:54.196
I got a <i>PAW Patrol</i> Band-Aid
and some playground sand. too.

566
00:26:54.280 --> 00:26:56.240
Look. they call nonstop
when I'm not there.

567
00:26:56.324 --> 00:26:59.660
And when I am there.
it's. you know.

568
00:26:59.744 --> 00:27:03.789
7:00 a.m. weekend soccer games.
teacher conferences.

569
00:27:03.873 --> 00:27:05.916
scheduled sex with the wife.

570
00:27:07.001 --> 00:27:09.462
I am no longer my own man.

571
00:27:09.545 --> 00:27:11.630
And you wouldn't trade it
for anything in the world.

572
00:27:11.714 --> 00:27:14.216
Not for $65 million.

573
00:27:14.300 --> 00:27:16.385
You are a changed man.
O'Donnell.

574
00:27:17.928 --> 00:27:20.556
Yep. Maybe you should
give it a go. huh?

575
00:27:20.639 --> 00:27:22.141
Buy some land. start a family.

576
00:27:22.224 --> 00:27:24.560
You'd be the scariest guy
at PTA.

577
00:27:24.643 --> 00:27:26.771
but you'd be a good dad.

578
00:27:26.854 --> 00:27:29.231
- If I had land. I'd get four or five...
- Four or five dogs.

579
00:27:29.315 --> 00:27:33.527
You'd get four or five dogs.
no woman?

580
00:27:33.611 --> 00:27:35.780
Not even Dixon?

581
00:27:38.115 --> 00:27:41.077
She's a friend.

582
00:27:41.160 --> 00:27:42.870
Okay.

583
00:27:42.953 --> 00:27:45.247
Whatever you say.

584
00:27:45.331 --> 00:27:47.166
That was some dress. though.

585
00:27:49.543 --> 00:27:50.669
Hell of a dress.

586
00:27:53.214 --> 00:27:55.132
From Neagley. It's intermission.

587
00:27:55.216 --> 00:27:56.717
Dixon and Boyd are leaving now.

588
00:27:56.801 --> 00:27:58.803
There they are.

589
00:28:00.471 --> 00:28:02.431
That's one hell of a dress.

590
00:28:02.515 --> 00:28:04.600
My car's around the corner.
Does that work?

591
00:28:04.683 --> 00:28:06.394
I'll follow anywhere
you lead. gorgeous.

592
00:28:06.477 --> 00:28:09.772
- Well. let's go party.
- Okay.

593
00:28:09.855 --> 00:28:11.732
Look at her.

594
00:28:11.816 --> 00:28:15.027
Boyd didn't stand a chance.

595
00:28:15.111 --> 00:28:16.487
Neagley again.

596
00:28:16.570 --> 00:28:18.656
- She says my guy's in place.
- Mm.

597
00:28:18.739 --> 00:28:21.033
Hey. this friend of yours.

598
00:28:21.117 --> 00:28:22.660
He's gonna come through
for us. yeah?

599
00:28:22.743 --> 00:28:24.995
If he was in the Army.

600
00:28:25.079 --> 00:28:27.164
I'd have asked him
to join the 110th.

601
00:28:32.753 --> 00:28:34.880
Come here. Mmm...

602
00:28:34.964 --> 00:28:36.924
- Oh. you're all riled up.
- Well. what can I say?

603
00:28:37.007 --> 00:28:38.717
Classical music
gets my motor running.

604
00:28:38.801 --> 00:28:41.178
Yeah. well. drop it to second.
Speed Racer.

605
00:28:41.262 --> 00:28:42.697
- Let's have a little primer first.
- Oh...

606
00:28:42.721 --> 00:28:44.723
You're not messing around.
All right.

607
00:28:44.807 --> 00:28:46.934
- There we go. Ooh. Ooh.
- Yeah. Yes.

608
00:28:47.017 --> 00:28:48.144
Okay. hold this. Hold...

609
00:28:48.227 --> 00:28:49.437
hold that.

610
00:28:52.523 --> 00:28:56.360
I never know how thick or thin
to make these things.

611
00:28:56.444 --> 00:28:58.821
- Hey. allow me.
- Thank you.

612
00:28:59.947 --> 00:29:02.700
Mm. Uh...

613
00:29:02.783 --> 00:29:04.785
Okay.
Ladies first?

614
00:29:04.869 --> 00:29:07.204
Oh. no. you did the work.
you get the reward.

615
00:29:07.288 --> 00:29:08.789
If you insist.

616
00:29:10.458 --> 00:29:12.585
Ooh!

617
00:29:14.670 --> 00:29:16.130
- Shit.
- Shit.

618
00:29:16.213 --> 00:29:17.566
- Just-just play it cool. just play it cool.
- Shit.

619
00:29:17.590 --> 00:29:19.175
Just play it cool.

620
00:29:21.886 --> 00:29:23.762
Sir. you're gonna want

621
00:29:23.846 --> 00:29:26.140
to put the drugs away
and step out of the car.

622
00:29:30.478 --> 00:29:32.897
- They're not my drugs.
- Which drugs...

623
00:29:32.980 --> 00:29:35.524
the ones on your mirror
or up your nose?

624
00:29:35.608 --> 00:29:38.444
You think I own a makeup
mirror? They're all hers.

625
00:29:38.527 --> 00:29:40.905
Not what she's saying.
and she wasn't holding it.

626
00:29:40.988 --> 00:29:43.782
And she already offered up
blood and urine.

627
00:29:43.866 --> 00:29:45.826
Do you want to offer up
blood and urine?

628
00:29:45.910 --> 00:29:50.122
Listen. Officer. I hate
putting it this way. but...

629
00:29:50.206 --> 00:29:51.749
do you know who I am?

630
00:29:51.832 --> 00:29:53.959
I do. actually. Mr. Boyd.

631
00:29:54.043 --> 00:29:57.630
And I know that woman in the car
wasn't Mrs. Boyd.

632
00:29:57.713 --> 00:30:01.550
And I have a special distaste
for people

633
00:30:01.634 --> 00:30:04.595
who don't appreciate
the sanctity of marriage.

634
00:30:05.888 --> 00:30:08.349
I also know you work
for Senator Lavoy.

635
00:30:08.432 --> 00:30:10.017
But when I ran your name
in the system.

636
00:30:10.100 --> 00:30:13.729
it set off bells and whistles
at the local FBI office.

637
00:30:13.812 --> 00:30:16.774
They sent a couple of their boys
down here just to talk to you.

638
00:30:16.857 --> 00:30:21.278
And it seems they don't care
who your boss is.

639
00:30:21.362 --> 00:30:22.988
Come on.

640
00:30:26.617 --> 00:30:28.994
Special Agent Jack Margrave.

641
00:30:30.162 --> 00:30:32.164
This is Special Agent Blake.

642
00:30:32.248 --> 00:30:33.791
Lieutenant Oscar Finlay.

643
00:30:33.874 --> 00:30:35.918
Yeah. I'm not talking
without my lawyer.

644
00:30:37.211 --> 00:30:38.754
You want to lawyer up?

645
00:30:38.837 --> 00:30:40.881
- Fine. Call them.
- I will.

646
00:30:40.965 --> 00:30:43.092
And they'll have me
out of here within the hour.

647
00:30:43.175 --> 00:30:45.219
Hmm. You know...

648
00:30:47.096 --> 00:30:48.681
...that's just
gonna be too late.

649
00:30:48.764 --> 00:30:50.349
Because by the time
they get here.

650
00:30:50.432 --> 00:30:51.767
we'll already have the story

651
00:30:51.850 --> 00:30:53.227
of a senator's
legislative director

652
00:30:53.310 --> 00:30:55.271
in the wrong woman's car

653
00:30:55.354 --> 00:30:57.064
with a snout
full of booger sugar

654
00:30:57.147 --> 00:31:00.276
on the front page
of the <i>Globe</i> and the <i>Herald.</i>

655
00:31:00.359 --> 00:31:02.653
You see.

656
00:31:02.736 --> 00:31:06.824
this is not college
or law school. son.

657
00:31:06.907 --> 00:31:09.618
You're not some spoiled rich kid
barely rocking a C-plus.

658
00:31:09.702 --> 00:31:11.495
You're a Beltway man now.

659
00:31:11.579 --> 00:31:12.955
Kind of guy that people

660
00:31:13.038 --> 00:31:14.915
enjoy knocking down
a peg or two.

661
00:31:14.999 --> 00:31:16.959
So these charges.

662
00:31:17.042 --> 00:31:19.587
they're not just gonna
get swept under the rug.

663
00:31:19.670 --> 00:31:21.005
We're not gonna let 'em.

664
00:31:21.088 --> 00:31:23.632
- Want to know why?
- Okay. Why?

665
00:31:23.716 --> 00:31:25.050
'Cause we don't like you.

666
00:31:25.134 --> 00:31:26.319
I don't even know

667
00:31:26.343 --> 00:31:27.779
- why you're here.
- We're here

668
00:31:27.803 --> 00:31:31.390
'cause we want to know
everything there is to know

669
00:31:31.473 --> 00:31:32.891
about Little Wing.

670
00:31:41.108 --> 00:31:42.669
- I should probably...
- Yeah. you should.

671
00:31:42.693 --> 00:31:45.154
Yeah. I'm gonna
call Mr. Boyd's wife.

672
00:31:45.237 --> 00:31:47.239
Eh. she's probably worried
about him over in D.C.

673
00:31:47.323 --> 00:31:48.657
Worried sick.

674
00:31:48.741 --> 00:31:50.176
You know. happy wife.
happy life. huh?

675
00:31:50.200 --> 00:31:52.119
Okay. Fine.

676
00:31:52.202 --> 00:31:53.829
<i>- Hello?</i>
- Wrong number.

677
00:31:53.912 --> 00:31:57.207
- Talk.
- It's not that big of a deal.

678
00:31:57.291 --> 00:31:58.834
Little Wing is just a code name.

679
00:31:58.917 --> 00:32:00.836
- For what?
- For a new technology

680
00:32:00.919 --> 00:32:02.755
currently in development.

681
00:32:02.838 --> 00:32:04.548
Some incredible
anti-missile software

682
00:32:04.632 --> 00:32:07.468
originally developed
to protect commercial aircraft.

683
00:32:07.551 --> 00:32:10.054
but a certain aeronautics
company approached us.

684
00:32:10.137 --> 00:32:12.973
Let me guess... New Age?

685
00:32:13.057 --> 00:32:14.683
That's right. New Age.

686
00:32:14.767 --> 00:32:16.518
They found the software
could be tweaked.

687
00:32:16.602 --> 00:32:19.563
It could be used in missiles
and not just against them.

688
00:32:19.647 --> 00:32:21.899
It could be scaled down
and installed

689
00:32:21.982 --> 00:32:25.027
in portable shoulder-fired
surface-to-air weaponry.

690
00:32:25.110 --> 00:32:26.945
The software allows missiles

691
00:32:27.029 --> 00:32:29.782
to defeat all known
countermeasures.

692
00:32:29.865 --> 00:32:31.617
- How?
- That's a question

693
00:32:31.700 --> 00:32:33.118
for a nerd in a lab coat. man.

694
00:32:33.202 --> 00:32:36.830
Okay? All I know is that
missiles shot from the ground

695
00:32:36.914 --> 00:32:38.874
completely bypass their target.

696
00:32:38.957 --> 00:32:41.210
making pilots believe
the threat has passed.

697
00:32:41.293 --> 00:32:43.921
and then they recalibrate.
turn around.

698
00:32:44.004 --> 00:32:46.298
zero back in on the aircraft
and reattack.

699
00:32:46.382 --> 00:32:49.843
It's death from above
and there is no way to avoid it.

700
00:32:49.927 --> 00:32:52.388
You fire. you hit your target.

701
00:32:52.471 --> 00:32:54.098
Period.

702
00:32:56.725 --> 00:32:58.644
And what's Senator Lavoy's
involvement?

703
00:32:58.727 --> 00:33:01.355
Well. the project required an
appropriation bill. all right?

704
00:33:01.438 --> 00:33:02.773
You want to get one passed?

705
00:33:02.856 --> 00:33:05.526
You're looking at years
of bureaucratic bullshit

706
00:33:05.609 --> 00:33:09.238
all thanks to some arcane laws
on modifying civilian tech.

707
00:33:09.321 --> 00:33:12.074
But Lavoy knew Little Wing
would slingshot

708
00:33:12.157 --> 00:33:16.203
our military into the future.
so if we just sat on our hands.

709
00:33:16.286 --> 00:33:18.330
waiting for it to go through
the proper channels.

710
00:33:18.414 --> 00:33:20.999
it would never happen.

711
00:33:21.083 --> 00:33:23.127
So I'm assuming Lavoy
didn't clear up the red tape

712
00:33:23.210 --> 00:33:25.421
in the most reputable manner?

713
00:33:25.504 --> 00:33:28.674
I helped bury the proposal
in a thousand-page statute

714
00:33:28.757 --> 00:33:30.360
while Lavoy shook hands
and drummed up votes.

715
00:33:30.384 --> 00:33:32.010
No one even knew
it was in there.

716
00:33:32.094 --> 00:33:35.139
And he did this out of
the goodness of his heart?

717
00:33:35.222 --> 00:33:37.516
To protect democracy?

718
00:33:37.599 --> 00:33:41.562
No fat envelopes slipped inside
newspapers on park benches?

719
00:33:41.645 --> 00:33:43.272
Grow the fuck up. okay?

720
00:33:43.355 --> 00:33:46.233
It's D.C.
It's how shit gets done.

721
00:33:46.316 --> 00:33:49.528
Besides. Lavoy knew Little Wing
would save lives.

722
00:33:49.611 --> 00:33:51.155
I mean...

723
00:33:51.238 --> 00:33:53.907
everyone made fun of
the <i>Star Wars</i> defense program.

724
00:33:53.991 --> 00:33:56.493
but. hey. look at where
we are now.

725
00:33:56.577 --> 00:33:59.705
Everyone's trying to shoot
projectiles out of the air.

726
00:33:59.788 --> 00:34:03.208
Little Wing can knock
anything out of the sky.

727
00:34:06.587 --> 00:34:09.840
Anything?
Like commercial aircraft?

728
00:34:09.923 --> 00:34:12.551
You fire. you hit the target.
You said so yourself.

729
00:34:12.634 --> 00:34:14.887
Yeah. but it's our tech.
We have it.

730
00:34:14.970 --> 00:34:17.139
Nobody else can
get their hands on it.

731
00:34:17.222 --> 00:34:19.308
Nothing like you're thinking
is going to happen.

732
00:34:19.391 --> 00:34:22.227
New Age is incredibly secure.
Both of their facilities

733
00:34:22.311 --> 00:34:24.646
- implement state-of-the-art...
- Both facilities?

734
00:34:25.981 --> 00:34:28.442
- What do you mean?
- New Age has two bases.

735
00:34:28.525 --> 00:34:29.860
Software made in New York.

736
00:34:29.943 --> 00:34:32.362
hardware at
a manufacturing plant in Denver.

737
00:34:32.446 --> 00:34:34.281
- What else can you tell us?
- Nothing.

738
00:34:34.364 --> 00:34:36.408
That's all I know. I swear.

739
00:34:37.659 --> 00:34:40.162
Hey. Lavoy and me...
we-we cut some corners.

740
00:34:40.245 --> 00:34:42.456
we did some stuff
we should not have done.

741
00:34:42.539 --> 00:34:45.334
but it was all to get
a defense bill passed.

742
00:34:45.417 --> 00:34:47.294
protect the country.

743
00:34:47.377 --> 00:34:49.379
How'd that work out?

744
00:34:49.463 --> 00:34:51.131
Hey. excuse me.

745
00:34:51.215 --> 00:34:54.843
So. are the drug charges
getting dropped or what?

746
00:34:54.927 --> 00:34:58.138
I don't know. I'm not a cop.

747
00:35:06.104 --> 00:35:08.148
Heck of a surprise
getting a call from you.

748
00:35:08.232 --> 00:35:11.360
Hell of a surprise hearing
you're wearing the badge again.

749
00:35:11.443 --> 00:35:12.986
Lieutenant. no less.

750
00:35:13.070 --> 00:35:15.113
Yeah. well.
retirement didn't suit me.

751
00:35:15.197 --> 00:35:18.575
Speaking of suits. see
you're still sporting the tweed.

752
00:35:20.118 --> 00:35:21.578
Reliable as ever. Finlay.

753
00:35:21.662 --> 00:35:23.413
Speak for yourself.

754
00:35:23.497 --> 00:35:25.833
What was it you told me
when we first met...

755
00:35:25.916 --> 00:35:28.293
trouble always seems
to find you?

756
00:35:29.920 --> 00:35:31.630
You kill a whole lot of people?

757
00:35:31.713 --> 00:35:33.090
Here and there.

758
00:35:33.173 --> 00:35:35.884
- You need my help?
- Already gave it.

759
00:35:35.968 --> 00:35:38.720
You still spinning
that wedding ring?

760
00:35:41.515 --> 00:35:44.977
Here and there.
But feeling better every day.

761
00:35:45.060 --> 00:35:47.062
- And the dog?
- Jack eats too much.

762
00:35:47.145 --> 00:35:48.605
Just like his namesake.

763
00:35:48.689 --> 00:35:50.148
Today. boss.

764
00:35:50.232 --> 00:35:51.900
Car's running.
and if I don't get out

765
00:35:51.984 --> 00:35:54.069
of this straitjacket soon.
things are gonna get ugly.

766
00:35:54.152 --> 00:35:55.988
Neagley?

767
00:35:56.071 --> 00:35:58.824
Didn't recognize you.
Looking good.

768
00:35:58.907 --> 00:36:01.076
Mind your business.
elbow patches.

769
00:36:02.828 --> 00:36:04.288
Hey. you heard the lady.

770
00:36:04.371 --> 00:36:07.040
If I don't have her in jeans
in 20 minutes.

771
00:36:07.124 --> 00:36:08.876
I'm done for.

772
00:36:09.918 --> 00:36:11.336
See you around. Reacher.

773
00:36:11.420 --> 00:36:13.338
See you around. Finlay.

774
00:36:24.099 --> 00:36:26.351
So. Little Wing
could be our next 9/11.

775
00:36:26.435 --> 00:36:29.146
- What are our directives?
- You and Dixon go to Denver.

776
00:36:29.229 --> 00:36:30.731
The Little Wing software
is useless

777
00:36:30.814 --> 00:36:32.542
without the missile hardware.
and that's where it's made.

778
00:36:32.566 --> 00:36:33.901
Maybe you can gum up the works.

779
00:36:33.984 --> 00:36:35.861
keep the missiles
out of the wrong hands.

780
00:36:35.944 --> 00:36:38.864
O'Donnell and I
will head down to D.C.

781
00:36:38.947 --> 00:36:42.159
Want to swing by Homeland.
see what they know about A.M.

782
00:36:42.242 --> 00:36:43.469
If taking out airplanes
is his M.O..

783
00:36:43.493 --> 00:36:44.828
they might have
some intel on him.

784
00:36:44.912 --> 00:36:46.556
How do you figure
we're gonna do that?

785
00:36:46.580 --> 00:36:47.891
You think we're just gonna
knock on the door

786
00:36:47.915 --> 00:36:50.083
and say. "Can the DoD
come out and play?"

787
00:36:50.167 --> 00:36:52.669
My brother worked for Homeland.

788
00:36:52.753 --> 00:36:54.338
His contacts can help us.

789
00:36:54.421 --> 00:36:57.132
Oh. no shit.
How's Joe doing these days?

790
00:36:57.215 --> 00:36:58.425
He's dead.

791
00:37:03.430 --> 00:37:06.725
I'm starving. We should eat.

792
00:37:24.618 --> 00:37:27.120
Dibs on the bathroom.

793
00:37:27.204 --> 00:37:28.973
I need to get changed.

794
00:37:28.997 --> 00:37:30.516
Yeah? You gonna
throw it in the garbage

795
00:37:30.540 --> 00:37:32.334
like our sociopathic friend
here?

796
00:37:32.417 --> 00:37:33.752
Oh. why. you want to borrow it?

797
00:37:33.835 --> 00:37:35.462
Oh. yeah. I got the ass for it.

798
00:37:47.975 --> 00:37:50.310
Hate to ruin prom night.

799
00:37:50.394 --> 00:37:51.728
but hand over your guns.

800
00:37:51.812 --> 00:37:53.730
What makes you think
we have guns?

801
00:37:53.814 --> 00:37:56.066
We were told
you'd be packing. Reacher.

802
00:38:01.697 --> 00:38:03.156
They also tell you

803
00:38:03.240 --> 00:38:04.950
you'd die tonight?

804
00:38:06.243 --> 00:38:08.453
I'll die? That's funny.

805
00:38:14.584 --> 00:38:16.837
No guns. so no noise.

806
00:38:16.920 --> 00:38:18.338
They said
you were smart.

807
00:38:18.422 --> 00:38:21.466
I'm gonna cut you. gut you

808
00:38:21.550 --> 00:38:22.551
and leave you...

809
00:39:11.808 --> 00:39:13.351
Aah!

810
00:39:47.135 --> 00:39:48.595
Everyone okay?

811
00:39:48.678 --> 00:39:50.722
Yeah. It'll heal.

812
00:39:52.557 --> 00:39:53.934
Never better.

813
00:39:54.017 --> 00:39:57.354
Fucked up my shoes.
but I'm fine.

814
00:40:10.158 --> 00:40:12.327
<i>- Yeah.</i>
- Before you ask if it's done.

815
00:40:12.410 --> 00:40:15.372
it is. just not in the way
you hoped for.

816
00:40:15.455 --> 00:40:19.167
You're causing a very complex
operation a lot of problems.

817
00:40:19.251 --> 00:40:21.795
Sixty-five million dollars
worth. Langston?

818
00:40:21.878 --> 00:40:24.005
Assume that's who
I'm talking to.

819
00:40:24.089 --> 00:40:25.924
Head of security?

820
00:40:26.007 --> 00:40:28.176
Head of this whole thing?

821
00:40:28.260 --> 00:40:31.805
Maybe we've been approaching
this the wrong way. Mr. Reacher.

822
00:40:31.888 --> 00:40:34.057
Just Reacher.

823
00:40:34.141 --> 00:40:37.144
<i>Okay. Reacher.
Why don't we make a deal?</i>

824
00:40:37.227 --> 00:40:42.232
I have the means to give you
anything you could ask for.

825
00:40:42.315 --> 00:40:44.901
What is it that you want?

826
00:40:47.154 --> 00:40:49.906
I want to throw you
out of a helicopter.

826
00:40:50.305 --> 00:41:50.179
